<HEADLINE> Large Tanker for Chemicals Launched In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- A 13,450-ton oil and chemical
tanker was launched today in Shanghai by the Jiangnan Shipyard
(Group).
</P>
<P>
It is equipped with a new type heating system that can
effectively prevent damage to the ship's engine by toxic
chemicals, and improve the ship's ability to operate under heavy
ice conditions.
</P>
<P>
Painting equipment imported from Singapore helped give the
tanker a better quality coating of paint.
</P>
<P>
The Jiangnan Shipyard is now building five chemical tankers of
the same kind for Sweden and Norway.  
</P>
</TEXT>
