<HEADLINE> International Flora Resources Seminar In Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Second International
Seminar on Flora Resources opened today in the capital of China's
Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from China, Britain, the United States and seven
Asian countries are attending the seminar to discuss research and
development in flora resources, nature protection, flora
diversification, and forest and environment regulations.
</P>
<P>
Flora diversification was understood by people in the distant
past, the scientists pointed out, but it has been damaged severely
by increasing human activities and the destruction of forests in
recent decades.
</P>
<P>
East and Southeast Asia have some of the richest flora
resources, the scientists said and asked the whole world to make
an effort in environmental protection and developing flora
resources.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is sponsored by the Chinese Academy of Sciences'
Kunming Plant Research Institute. The first seminar of this kind
was held in the city ten years ago.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
