<HEADLINE> 146 Kilograms of Narcotics Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police seized 99.6
kilograms of heroin and 46.5 kilograms of hashish in their recent
operations against drug trafficking in eastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The narcotics were captured in Yuksekova town in Hakkari
province linking neighboring Iran, the semi-official Anatolia News
Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the operations, 13 people in connection with the drugs were
taken into custody.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs from the border areas of
Afghanistan and Parkistan to Europe. In 1996, Turkish police
seized 4.4 tonnes of heroin, which accounted for 40 percent of the
world's total haul. 
</P>
</TEXT>
