<HEADLINE> Coach Van Hanegem Extends Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Willem van Hanegem renewed
his contract as coach of Dutch first division squad AZ Alkmaar by
five years, according to ANP from Amsterdam, the Netherlands, on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The former Dutch international midfielder said last week he
would quit AZ at the end of the season as he could not agree on
the financial terms of extending his current contract.
</P>
<P>
ANP said contract talks were resumed after vociferous protests
by disgruntled AZ fans.
</P>
<P>
Van Hanegem joined AZ last year after coaching stints with
Feyenoord, FC Wageningen and Saudi Arabian club Al Hilal. He
guided the second division side to promotion in his first season
in charge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
