<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Defense Minister Denies Arms Sale Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Defense Minister Georgi
Ananiev said Tuesday that his country had never sold weapons to
embargoed countries.
</P>
<P>
He made the denial in response to questions about a press
report on the Troud newspaper, which carried a story Tuesday with
the headline "U.S. Angry at Bulgaria Selling Tanks", detailing
alleged sales of tanks to Ethiopia and Uganda.
</P>
<P>
"We do not sell weapons to embargoed countries," the minister
said, adding that Bulgaria was honoring its commitments to dispose
of the armaments which were in excess of its assigned quotas in
accordance with international agreements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
