<HEADLINE> Finland to Open Representative Office in Palestine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Finland will open a
representative office in Palestine on January 1, 1999, to promote
relations with Palestine, the Foreign Ministry announced on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The main mission of the office will be to help provide economic
assistance for Palestine.
</P>
<P>
Finland has agreed to provide a package of aid worth 45 million
Finnish markka (nine million U.S. dollars) for Palestine following
up on assistance worth of 80 million markka (16 million dollars).
It also provides 10 million markka (two million dollars) for
Palestine through the United Nations Relief Work Agency for
Palestinian refugees.
</P>
<P>
Most of the assistance is used to improve water supply systems
and develop education.
</P>
<P>
Finland will be the fifth European Union country to establish a
representative office in Palestine.  
</P>
</TEXT>
