<HEADLINE> New Talks on Sudan to Be Held in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 8 (Xinhua) -- A new round of talks between
the Sudanese government and the Sudanese People's Liberation
Movement (SPLM) is scheduled to be held in Nairobi, Kenya in
January next year, Sudanese Foreign Minister Gabriel Roric Jur
announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Bishop Gabriel Roric Jur, who is attending the eighth World
Council of Churches Assembly in Harare, told a press conference
that the talks would be in line with the Addis Ababa ceasefire
agreement signed in early August.
</P>
