stipulated that the two parties meet after six months to iron out
any outstanding issues toward a peaceful solution.
</P>
<P>
"We are looking forward to meeting in January in Nairobi on
points that were not agreed on in Addis Ababa," said Roric Jur.
</P>
<P>
SPLM leader John Garang has been fighting the predominantly
Islamic government since 1955. The war has caused the death and
displacement of millions of people as successive governments fail
to reach a lasting solution with the SPLM. 
