<HEADLINE> U.S. Special Envoy in Ethiopia for Mediation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Former United States
National Security Adviser and special presidential envoy Anthony
Lake returned here on Tuesday from Asmara to continue his
mediation between the two Horn of Africa countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, Lake, who is on his
third attempt to facilitate a peaceful solution to the
seven-month Ethio-Eritrean border dispute, is expected to meet
Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles Zenawi Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The former U.S. National Security Adviser met with Meles last
Saturday before leaving for Asmara, capital of Eritrea, for talks
with Eritrean officials.
</P>
<P>
Lake started his third mediation effort last week. His two
previous visits to Addis Ababa were on October 8 and November 11.
</P>
<P>
The summit of the Organization of African Unity (OAU)
mediation committee on Ethio-Eritrean border dispute, held in
Ouagadougou of Burkina Faso on November 7 and 8, came up with a
set of proposals on the peaceful solution to the border dispute.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has accepted the OAU proposals while Eritrea rejected
the key element of the peace plan which calls for the withdrawal
of its troops from the disputed Badme area.
</P>
<P>
The proposals will be submitted to the summit of Central Organ
of OAU Mechanism for Conflict Prevention, Management and
Resolution which is scheduled to be held in Ouagadougou on
December 17 and 18. 
</P>
