company which in turn transferred them to Salim Saleh, President
Yoweri Museveni's brother and senior presidential advisor on
defense and security.
</P>
<P>
Saleh reportedly admitted buying UCB through Greenland Bank
secretly because according to the agreement, the Malaysian
company is not allowed to sell the shares to a third party.
</P>
<P>
The UCB scandal forced Saleh to resign on Saturday, a headline
story that drew attention from all people in the capital city.
