<HEADLINE> Egypt, Mozambique to Boost Bilatenral Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and Mozambique Tuesday
underlined the need to further promote bilateral cooperation in a
bid to make use of the potentials of the two sides to enhance
trade exchange.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique issued at the end of the first session of
the Egyptian-Mozambican Joint Higher Committee held here, the two
countries expressed satisfaction for their existing "profound
cooperation ties."
</P>
<P>
They welcomed the increasing bilateral cooperation in the
fields of health, education, agriculture, police, social work and
banking, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
It called for the need to encourage the participation of
businessmen of the two countries in the bilateral economic and
trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to set up a mechanism for cooperation
between the foreign ministries of the two countries for
consultations and coordination of stances, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
As for regional and international issues, the two countries
reiterated commitment to the principles and targets of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) and the United Nations as they
represent a suitable framework for enhancing peace and cooperation
in Africa and the world over.
</P>
<P>
The two African countries voiced readiness to continue efforts
to help end disputes in Africa through endorsement of OAU's
mechanism for settling disputes peacefully.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa and his Mozambican
counterpart Leonardo Simao co-chaired the meeting, during which
they signed an agreement on encouraging and protecting investments
and another on technical and technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican official arrived here Sunday for a three-day
visit. 
</P>
