<HEADLINE> Ethiopian President Calls to Ensure Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian President
Negasso Gidada called on the Ethiopian people Tuesday to ensure
that development activities are undertaken uninterrupted.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion of the fourth anniversary of the
Federal Constitution here, Negasso said one of the major
objectives of the nation's Constitution is to overcome economic
backwardness by mobilizing the people in development leading them
to sustainable and steady growth.
</P>
<P>
He said the Constitution, in addition to promoting a
democratic system in the country, has also made decisive
contributions for consolidating the unity of the people and
nurturing the spirit of Ethiopianness and patriotism.
</P>
<P>
The president described as "quite encouraging" the activities
undertaken during the past couple of years with regard to
familiarizing the populace with constitutional rights.
</P>
<P>
