<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Approves German Companies' Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) said
here Tuesday that it has approved a major merger of German
companies.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the EU's executive body, said the
merger deals with the acquisition of the German state-owned
Autobahn Tank &AMP; Rast AG by a consortium of Allianz Capital
Partners GmbH, a german insurance company, LSG Lufthansa, the
national airway company, and three investment trusts.
</P>
<P>
The commission said the Tank &AMP; Rast owns most of the plots of
land on which the German motorway service areas are located. It
makes profits by leasing the vast majority of motorway service
areas along Germany's motorways.
</P>
<P>
The EU said the merger will not change market conditions given
that it consists only in a change of shareholders, therefore it
has decided not to oppose the notified operation and to declare
the merger compatible with the common market and with the European
Economic Area.
</P>
<P>
After completion of the merger, Lufthansa and Allianz will each
own 33.3 percent of the shares of the new company, Autobahn Tank &AMP;
Rast Holding GmbH. The remaining 33.3 percent of the shares will
be held by three Apax-fund companies who are also members of the
consortium but who have not the possibility to exercise control.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
