<HEADLINE> Chinese Asked To Save Trees By Sending Fewer Greeting Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Environmental
Protection Fund (CEPF), All-China Federation of Trade Unions,
Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Youth League, and
All-China Women's Federation started a "Fewer Cards To Save Trees"
action recently to make people more aware of environment
protection.
</P>
<P>
China's forests cover a mere 13.9 percent of the country, and
serious soil erosion is eating an area as large as Beijing every
eight years.
</P>
<P>
A CEPF study found that the people of Beijing send more than 30
million greeting cards between Christmas and the Spring Festival,
the traditional Chinese lunar New Year, equal to more than 10,000
trees and 300,000 kwh of electricity and 9,000 tons of polluted
water resulting from their production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
