<HEADLINE> EU Donates Food to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)
announced Wednesday it is donating a total of 1.85 million tons of
food to Russia.
</P>
<P>
The food aid, which will cost the EU 400 million European
Currency Units (440 million U.S. dollars), came in response to a
request from the Russian government.
</P>
<P>
The EU will provide one million tons of wheat, 500,000 tons of
rye, 50,000 tons of rice, 150,000 tons of beef, 100,000 tons of
pork, and 50,000 tons of skimmed milk powder.
</P>
<P>
With the exception of pork, which will be bought after seeking
tenders, EU will obtain the products from its intervention stocks.
</P>
<P>
The private operator responsible for the transport of the
products to Russia will also be chosen following a tender
procedure. 
