<HEADLINE> OAU Military Mission Arrives in Comoros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of
African Unity (OAU) announced here Wednesday that an OAU
military-security mission arrived in Moroni, capital of the
Comoros, in the day.
</P>
<P>
An OAU press release issued Wednesday said the
military-security team was sent urgently to the Federal Islamic
Republic of the Comoros following consultations between OAU
Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim and the South African
authorities as well as representatives from various African
countries of the region.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, Salim, who is currently on a
five-day visit to South Africa, met in Pretoria Tuesday evening
with the team of senior military and security officers from
Kenya, Mauritius, Mozambique, South Africa and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The team will make an assessment of the situation and submit
appropriate recommendations.
</P>
<P>
About dozens of people were killed in machine-gun and
artillery battle in Mutsamudu, Anjouan Island of the Comoros
since faction fighting broke out last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Comoros, which gained independence from France in
1975, lies about 320 kilometers off the east coast of Africa,
halfway between Mozambique and the Indian ocean island of
Madagascar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
