<HEADLINE> Beijing Symposium On The Euro And Sino-European Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Some Chinese and European
bankers and scholars meeting today at a conference on the euro and
Chinese-European business relations, agreed that China needs to
prepare for possible negative effects of the euro.
</P>
<P>
Chinese officials, scholars, European diplomats, and company
and bank representatives attended the conference, which is
sponsored by China's State Council's Development Research Center
and Handelsblatt, the German financial and business daily.
</P>
<P>
Participants held that after the euro goes into circulation in
the next few weeks, it will mean great changes in the current
international financial system initially and that China's foreign
trade and use of overseas investment will meet with some
unprecedented opportunities and challenges in the long run.
</P>
</TEXT>
