<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Getting Tough With Illegal Massage Parlors And Saunas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- China is planning a campaign to
crack down on illegal activities in massage parlors, sauna baths,
and beauty parlors from December 10 to April 30, according to a
circular issued by the Public Security, Labor and Social Security,
and Public Health ministries, and the State Administration for
Industry and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
In the circular they said that some of these places have been
engaged in illegal hirings and pornographic activities and that
people involved in the massage, beauty parlor, sauna, or
foot-washing business will be subject to scrutiny.
</P>
<P>
And, the words "medical care", "herbal bath", "Traditional
Chinese medical massage", or "foot-washing house" will not be
allowed to be used in ads associated with these places.
</P>
<P>
Anyone found to be engaging in illegal hiring practices and
prostitution will be punished in accordance with the law.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
