<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Undertakes Water Projects for 25 Towns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Water Resources said Wednesday that it has signed an agreement
with three international companies to undertake projects for the
provision of potable water for 25 towns.
</P>
<P>
The ministry told journalists that the agreement, worth 2.63
million U.S. Dollars, is part of the 65.5-million-Dollar potable
water development and rehabilitation program designed to ensure
the supply of safe drinking water to the whole country.
</P>
<P>
The three companies from Israel, Germany and Norway will
complete the feasibility study and design work in two years,
according to the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Some 35.7 million out of the 65.5 million Dollars will be
financed by a World Bank loan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
