<HEADLINE> Panda Breeding Seminar In Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The annual meeting of the China
Giant Panda Breeding Technical Committee opened today in the
capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Specialists and officials from Chinese zoos, the CBSG, the
U.S.'s Fish and Game Department, and U.S. state zoos have come for
the meeting to discuss a wide range of issues on protecting the
giant panda and its breeding habits, heredity and medical
examinations.
</P>
<P>
They will also be invited to visit the Giant Panda Breeding
Research Base and the Wolong Nature Reserve. 
</P>
