<HEADLINE> Colombo Municipal Councilor Assassinated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 9 (Xinhua) -- A Colombo municipal councilor
was assassinated Wednesday afternoon by an unknown assassin,
police said.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, Imtiaz of the ruling People's Alliance
was shot at about 3:45 p.m. local time at Maradana near Ananda
College. He died on the way to the National Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The police said Imtiaz was shot by an individual who had
arrived at the scene in a van. Imtiaz was in a three-wheeler with
another person.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the three-wheeler halted the vehicle and went
into a nearby boutique after Imtiaz was shot, police said.
</P>
<P>
The police are making further inquiries and the three-wheeler
driver has been arrested in this connection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
