<HEADLINE> China Beats Japan in Asiad Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Newly-crowned Asian champion
China overwhelmed its main rival Japan in the 13th Asian Games'
men's volleyball group match here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese received little resistance from the Japanese in the
first set which they won 15-3 with ease.
</P>
<P>
However, the Japanese came into life in the second set and
dominated the match in most of the time. Though the Chinese tried
to catch up, the Japanese took their revenge by winning the set
16-14.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese, though still not recovered from the World
Championships last month, showed hundreds of enthusiastic Thai
fans that they are the real No. 1 in Asia by winning the following
two sets 15-9 and 15-8.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Wang Jiawei said after the match that he was
quite satisfied with the performance of the players.
</P>
<P>
"If we can take the second set, I will be 100 percent
satisfied," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang said apart from the physical exhaustion, the Chinese
players were also under great psychological pressure from the
crown of Asian champion.
</P>
<P>
"Keeping the championship is more difficult than winning it.
You have to overpass yourself first," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
He said he was happy to see the Chinese young players showing
their best under such a circumstance.
</P>
<P>
Up till now, China won all the three group matches against
India, Pakistan and Japan in Pool B and will also meet Kazakhstan
in the same group.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, South Korea and Chinese Taipei also won their
respective matches in straight sets in Group A which includes
Thailand, Indonesia and Qatar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
