<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Steps Up Anti-Corruption Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev on Wednesday signed the country's first anti-corruption
law and action plan to press as part of a campaign against
corruption.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev ordered the government and its local branches at all
levels to ensure the implementation of the law and the plan over
the next two years.
</P>
<P>
He also directed the government to provide a budget for the
implementation of the plan and asked the presidential office to
oversee the implementation of the plan. 
