<DOCNO> XIE19981209.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reigning Champion Indonesia Sails into Badminton Semifinal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 9 (Xinhua) - Defending champion Indonesia
Wednsday slashed Hongkong, China 5-0 to join arch-rivals China,
South Korea and Malaysia in the semi-finals of the men's badminton
team event at the Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
In the women's sections, hot favorite China, who retained the
Uber Cup trophy by beating two-time champion Indonesia in May,
showed its strong bidding for the Asian title by overpowering
Hongkong, China 5-0 without dropping a single game.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese will take on the Japanese, who finished host
Thailand 4-1, in the semi-final on Thursday with the other
semi-final pitting Indonesia against South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia met stubborn resistance from Hongkong, China though
it sealed the match with the score of 5-0.
</P>
<P>
In the first two singles, Hendrawan, who enabled Indonesian
men's team to take the Thomas Cup by taking the winning point in
the final singles, and Taufik Hidayat were stretched three games
before demolishing Tam Kai-Chuen and Liu Kwok-Wa.
</P>
<P>
Chandra Wijaya and Tony Gunawan sealed his team victory by
winnng the first doubles over Chow Kin-Man and Yau Kwun-Yuen in
straight games. Budi Santoso from Indonesia beat NG Wei and
double pair Rexy Mainaky and Riky Subadjya had little problems
beating Ma Che-Kong and Liu Kwok-Wa in two games.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Cup runners-up Malaysia, dropping two top single and
double players, struggled to edge out the fighting Chinese Taipei
4-1.
</P>
<P>
China will take on South Korea while Indonesia plays Malaysia
in the semi-finals on Thursday in the men's tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
