<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Railway Transport Business Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- China's railway transport
business has been increasing since the Ministry of Railways
adopted several new measures including increased train speed and
improved services.
</P>
<P>
Trains carried a total of 77,200 cargo cars a day on average in
November, a monthly high for the year, according to ministry
statistics.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2.4 million passengers traveled by train daily on
average last month, including 604,000 passengers whose one-way
journeys exceeded 500 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Trains also transported 31,500 cars of coal and 298,200 TEUs
(twenty-foot equivalent units) of containers. The transport of
other key materials, such as oil, timber and cotton, all exceeded
their target amounts.
</P>
<P>
Many travelers have been turning to highways or air travel in
the past few years for faster and more comfortable service,
causing annual railway transport volume to plummet.
</P>
<P>
China will spend more than 40 billion yuan (4.83 billion US
dollars) to build railways this year, with an emphasis on railways
in southwestern China, such as the rail lines between Liupanshui
to the city of Zhuzhou, between Neijiang and Kunming, and between
Daxian county and Wanxian county. 
</P>
</TEXT>
