<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Economic Conference (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The conference called for attention to be paid to four major
issues for improving economic activities in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Firstly, while ensuring the continuation of an appropriately
paced economic growth, efforts should be focused on making the
best use of the existing economic structure while at the same time
improving the quality and efficiency of growth overall.
</P>
<P>
It is accepted that fairly fast growth can generate more jobs,
increase revenues, improve the living standards of people. It may
also contribute to solving problems arising from the current
reforms.
</P>
<P>
Taking into account the prevailing conditions of a socialist
market economy, the speed of economic development should be
measured and set against agreed forecasts and should be market-led
rather than imposed in a mandatory manner. It should also be based
on reality, be well coordinated and highly efficient.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, to improve domestic demand and expand the domestic
market will be a basic policy platform within a long-term economic
strategy.
</P>
<P>
While continuing to increase the central government's
investment, more measures will be taken to encourage the
investment portfolio of enterprises, collectives and individuals.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, further efforts will be made to expand urban and
rural markets and nurture new consumer hot spots to stimulate even
more consumption.
</P>
<P>
Thirdly, active fiscal and monetary policies will be
implemented with the aim of encouraging and domestic demand and
expand domestic market. A key task is to make sure that increased
investment funds will be used for infrastructure construction in
an efficient way.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, efforts will be introduced to assist the improvement
of tax collection.
</P>
<P>
Fourthly, the conference declared that close attention should
be paid to guaranteeing social and political stability, while
deepening the reforms and promoting economic development.
</P>
<P>
All Party members, especially leading Party officials at
different levels, should take economic work as the central issue
and firmly push forward the reform and opening drive, while
sticking to the Four Cardinal Principles.
</P>
<P>
The timing and extent of reform measures must always be well
thought out in accordance with the capacity of the public and with
due considerations on coordination between various
measures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981209.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial on Central Economic Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading newspaper, is to publish an editorial Thursday on the
Central Conference on Economic Work which was held in Beijing from
December 7-9.
</P>
<P>
The conference summed up the country's economic work in 1998,
analysed the current international and domestic situation, and
outlined the requirements for next year's economic work.
</P>
<P>
The editorial, titled "Being Determined and Pressing Forward
Despite Difficulties to Win New Victories in Reform and
Construction," hails the conference as important for pushing
forward the current reform and opening and the country's
socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The editorial praises the CPC Central Committee for its timely
and correct decision to tackle the difficult situation caused by
the financial turmoil in Asia and the devastating summer floods
through stimulating domestic demand and utilizing macroeconomic
means to achieve steady economic growth.
</P>
<P>
It attributes the remarkable achievements China has made in
1998 to the foundation laid by the 20-year-old reform and opening
drive, the timely and correct policy of the CPC Central Committee,
and the hard efforts made by the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Next year will be of special importance to the current reform and
opening and modernization drive and the history of the Party and
the nation, the editorial says, adding that economic work in 1999
will be of great importance as well.
</P>
<P>
In order to achieve sustained, speedy and healthy economic
development, the conference put forward some general requirements
for 1999. It called for enlarged domestic demand, stabilized and
reinforced agriculture, restructured state enterprises, increased
exports, and minimized financial risks.
</P>
<P>
The editorial urged recognition of both the favorable and
negative sides of the current international and domestical
situation, and a deeper understand of central economic policies.
</P>
<P>
It also called for relying on the masses in order to bring
their enthusiasm and creativity into full play and urged leading
officials at all levels to be concerned with the life of the
masses, especially factory layoffs in cities and people living in
disaster-stricken and poverty areas. The leaders should remain
forthright, go deep into the grassroot units, and work with the
masses, it stresses.
</P>
<P>
The Party's leadership in the area of economic work should be
strengthened and improved, the editorial said, noting that China
is carrying out its socialist modernization drive while the world
is tending toward multi-polarization and economic globalization.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
