<HEADLINE> S. Korean Diver Injured in Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 9 (Xinhua) -- South Korean diver Cho Dae-Don
was hospitalised here on Wednesday when he chafed his foot against
the board in the men's three-meter springboard preliminary.
</P>
<P>
"His injury is not serious," said South Korean diving coach
Park Yoo-Hyun. "He received five stichese and now is all right,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Cho banged his right foot against the board in his second dive,
and was sent to hospital with his injured foot bleeding.
</P>
<P>
This accident is a reminiscent of the scene in the 1988
Olympics when Greg Louganis of the United States injured his foot
in the diving competition, which aroused great panic among South
Koreans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
