<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Economic Conference (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The management of enterprises will be strengthened. Meanwhile
the traditional assessment of leaders' performance by workers'
representatives will be maintained. Conference delegates were told
that the reform of small state-owned enterprises should not be
dictated simply by sales figures. Firm measures will be taken to
prevent the loss of state assets as well as avoiding the
invalidation of financial bonds issued by enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Thirdly, the main financial task for 1999 is to maintain the
stability of the yuan in order to support economic development and
avoid and minimize financial risks.
</P>
<P>
Financial reforms, especially those of state commercial banks
will be accelerated to assist in the setting up a financial
mechanism in line with development of a socialist market
economy. Stringent efforts will be made to rectify any financial
disorder, enhance regulation of the financial sector and formulate
efficient financial laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
The conference recommended that the existing strategy for
revitalizing China through the development of science, technology
and education should continue. Enterprises should give top
priority to promoting the upgrading of technology, transforming
traditional industries with high technology and creating more
high-tech firms in the future.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the country every possible means to increase exports
and raise the volume of trade should be tried. Foreign trade
departments are required to introduce a strategy for exploring all
possible markets, to adjust export mix to forge new markets while
consolidating exports in their traditional and existing markets.
</P>
<P>
The conference agreed that proper guidance is needed for foreign
investment which must be used efficiently and effectively.
</P>
<P>
The management of foreign exchanges will be improved to maintain
a basic balance in international payments.
</P>
<P>
And the delegates were told that the ongoing struggle against
smuggling will be maintained indefinitely.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
