<HEADLINE> Australian FM to Visit 5 South Pacific Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Australian Foreign Affairs
Minister Alexander Downer will visit five South Pacific nations
starting Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Downer will visit Papua New Guinea, Solomon Islands, Kiribati,
Tuvalu and Fiji in his fourth trip to the region as foreign
affairs minister, a foreign affairs department spokesman said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the nine-day visit, Downer will urge members of the
Forum Fisheries Agency, which also includes Australia and New
Zealand, to abide by their recent agreement on a vessel monitoring
system.
</P>
<P>
Downer will begin his trip to Port Moresby, capital of Papua
New Guinea, where he will dine with Prime Minister Bill Skate.
</P>
<P>
While in Papua New Guinea, he will open a hospital and an
airstrip on Buka Island, both completed with Australian government
assistance as part of the Bougainville rehabilitation program.
</P>
<P>
Downer also intends to use his visit to discuss with Solomon
Islands' Prime Minister Ulufa'alu about ways of taking the
Bougainville peace process further.
</P>
<P>
Downer will also attend the annual Australia-Fiji ministerial
talks in Nadi on December 18 on issues including bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
Downer will also use his trip to launch Australia's new Pacific
Islands Development Strategy, the first comprehensive three-year
strategy for Australia's aid to the island countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
