<HEADLINE> Preparatory Meetings for ASEAN Summit Held in Hanoi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN senior officials held
meetings here on December 8-9 in preparation for the Sixth ASEAN
Summit scheduled for next week.
</P>
<P>
These meetings included ASEAN directors-general meeting (ASEAN
DG), ASEAN senior officials meeting (SOM) and ASEAN senior
economic meeting (SEOM).
</P>
<P>
According to a press release here Wednesday afternoon, the
ASEAN DG meeting considered the draft report of the ASEAN foreign
and economic ministers which is to be submitted to the heads of
ASEAN state/government, the DRAFT Hanoi Declaration of 1998 and
Hanoi Plan of Action to implement the ASEAN Vision 2020.
</P>
<P>
The meeting agreed with portions of those drafts relating to
the functional aspects, which will be submitted to the ministerial
meetings for consideration.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also considered the agenda, program of activities
and other arrangements for the 6th ASEAN Summit and ASEAN plus
Summit meetings with China, Japan and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
The SOM and the SEOM considered the political portion and the
economic portion of above-mentioned documents.
</P>
<P>
The SOM agreed to the agenda and lists of main topics to be
submitted to the leaders for their discussion at the summit and
ASEAN plus summit meetings with China, Japan and the Republic of
Korea.
</P>
<P>
The SEOM discussed various measures to bring about early
economic recovery and further enhance ASEAN economic integration.
</P>
</TEXT>
