<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cause of Human Rights Faces Progress and Challenges (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In order to promote full-dimension development of the human
rights cause, the international community have to take equal
account of experiences and contributions made by both the
developed and developing countries. More attention should be given
to the experiences of the developing countries and the efforts
they made in protecting human rights and fundamental freedom of
their people, he said.
</P>
<P>
Dong also urged that special attention should be paid to
creating an international environment in favor of development of
the human rights cause.
</P>
<P>
Realization of human rights is closely linked with world peace
and development of the world. Peace and development are the two
top concerns of the world and the prerequisite for the realization
of universal human rights and fundamental freedom, he said.
</P>
<P>
Without peace, a stable international environment, and a just
and reasonable economic order, realization of universal human
rights is impossible, he said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, so long as the international community pays equal
attention to protecting human rights, maintaining world peace and
promoting development, genuine and gradual development of the
human rights protection would be realizable, he said.
</P>
<P>
The goals and principles set in the U.N. Charter should be well
kept up, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Charter holds correctly that the fundamental way for
promoting human rights protection is "promoting international
cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
Given the different histories and varied development condition,
it is normal that various countries make different approaches in
human rights protection, he said.
</P>
<P>
The only and correct solution in this regard is dialogue,
cooperation, seeking common ground while observing differences and
improving mutual understanding according to the principle of
equality and mutual respect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
