<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks gained 10.21
points, or 0.10 percent, to close at 10,361.29 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Market turnover was 4.581 billion HK dollars (587 million U.S.
dollars), 399 million HK dollars (51 million U.S. dollars) less
than that of Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index (HSI) fell 57.41 points, or 0.55
percent, to open at 10,293.67 Wednesday morning. It then dropped
99.05 points, or 0.96 percent, to close the morning session at
10,252.03.
</P>
<P>
