<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Rate Hits 5.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in Macao
rose to 5.4 percent between August and October this year, latest
official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released Wednesday by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department, the jobless rate increased 0.1 percent over
the July-September period this year.
</P>
<P>
During the August-October period last year, the jobless rate
stood at three percent.
</P>
<P>
Mounting unemployment rate since last year have aroused much
concern among local residents and economists, who expect that the
Macao government should cut the number of outside labors and work
out a more favorable economic policy. 
</P>
