<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Impose Levy on Windfall Profit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 9 (Xinhua) -- A bill to allow the
Malaysian government to impose a levy on windfall profit derived
from the production of goods was tabled in Parliament here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Tabling the Windfall Profit Levy Bill 1998, Deputy Finance
Minister Wong See Wah said, "The levy is imposed on a company for
profit derived from the exchange rate."
</P>
<P>
The bill would enforce a proposal contained in the 1999 budget
to impose a levy on windfall profit on production of unprocessed
palm oil and palm kernel oil, he said.
</P>
<P>
The bill also provides for a penalty of not more than 20,000
ringgit (5,263 U.S. dollars) or imprisonment of not more than one
year or both for offenses such as payment of levy less than the
amount determined by the finance minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
