<HEADLINE> Share Prices Surge on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices surged on a more
favorable interest rate scenario.
</P>
<P>
Talk of more interest rate cuts propelled the benchmark Straits
Times Index (STI) to run up 30.98 points to close at 1,424.59,
again breaching the 1,400-point level.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover was 261.61 million units worth 585.49 million
Singapore dollars (355.12 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
outnumbered losers by 168 to 92 with 159 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
CSA topped the actives chart of the day with a turnover of
37.81 million units traded. KepLand w00 was the second most
heavily traded share with a volume of 14.30 million units done.
KepBank was next with 9.84 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
OCBC F was the biggest gainer of the day with a 100-cent jump
to 11.60 Singapore dollars. OCBC picked up 75 cents to end at 6.90
Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem ran up 50 cents to finish at 9.20
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, RothmansI led the descent of the day with a
loss of 15 cents to 9.80 Singapore dollars. Jar Mat shed 11 cents
to close at 2.89 Singapore dollars. Jurship sank 10 cents to end
at 7.00 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was quieter than it had been over the
last two days as Wall Street decline put slight damper on buying.
</P>
<P>
They said renewed fund flow and expectations of interest rate
cuts were main factors that influenced the market.
</P>
<P>
Stronger regional currencies helped boost sentiment on the
local bourse, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
