<HEADLINE> Russia: Successful Test Launch of New ICBM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Strategic Missile
Force has successfully test-launched a new Topol-M
inter-continental ballistic missile from the Plesetsk launching
center in northern Russia, Interfax reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The launch reaffirmed the main flight and technical parameters
of the missile, which are unique to the Topol-M, and completed "a
key stage in developing the missile complex of the 21st century,"
the force's press service said.
</P>
<P>
This was the sixth test launch of the Topol-M missile.
</P>
<P>
"The task put forward by the supreme commander-in-chief and the
defense minister to develop and commission the Topol missile
system for the Strategic Nuclear Forces has been successfully
carried out," Force Commander Col. Gen. Vladimir Yakovlev said.
</P>
<P>
The first missile regiment equipped with the Topol-M in
Tatishchevo will come on duty this year, Yakovlev said. 
