<HEADLINE> Japan Wins Women's 63-kg Judo Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Nami Kimoto of Japan outwitted
her Chinese opponent Wang Xianbo to take the women's 63-kg judo
title at the 13th Asian Games here on Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Wang brought home the silver, while the bronze medal
was shared by Wu Mei-Ling of Chinese Taipei and Kim Hwa-Soo of
South Korea. 
</P>
