<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Outlines Economic Tasks for 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Agricultural development,
State-owned enterprise reform and financial work have been listed
as the key tasks for China's economic work in 1999, according to a
three-day central conference on economic work which ended here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
the State Council convened the annual Central Economic Conference
from December 7 to 9.
</P>
<P>
General Secretary of the CPC Central Committee Jiang Zemin
delivered an important speech at the meeting, in which he reviewed
the economic work in 1998, analyzed the present economic
situation, and outlined the overall requirements, key points and
major issues which need to be well handled in the coming year.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Rongji, premier and member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, made an important
speech at the meeting on the plan for the economic work in 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to the conference, big headway has been made in
China's economic restructuring, many reforms have been progressing
orderly on schedule in 1998 with significant progress achieved in
some difficult issues.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, China will continue to move forward with its reforms
and opening up drive, with the focus on expanding domestic demand
to promote economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be made to stabilize and reinforce agriculture,
deepen state-owned enterprise reforms, readjust the economic
structure, work hard to develop urban and rural markets, expand
export trade by every means, prevent and minimize financial risks
and straighten out the economic order, so as to maintain a
sustainable, fast and healthy development of the national economy
and an overall social progress.
</P>
<P>
Stress will be laid on the following three aspects: stabilize
and reinforce agriculture, deepen the state-owned enterprise
reforms, and do a good job of the financial work.
</P>
<P>
Among other Party and state leaders attending the conference
were Li Peng, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
