<HEADLINE> Chinese Wins Men's Air Pistol Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese shooters triumphed in
the men's air pistol shooting event at the Asian Games here on
Wednesday, finishing one-two in the individual competition and
taking the team title.
</P>
<P>
Asian champion Xu Dan, 29, produced a remarkable 103.0 points
in the grippling final to bring the total score to a winning 685.0
while his compatriot Tan Zongliang grabbed the silver at 683.6.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan's Vladimir Guchsha, who led the qualification with
583 points ahead of Xu's 582, won the bronze at 682.6. World
champion Wang Yifu finished fourth.
</P>
<P>
"Usually I shot better with the free pistol than with the air
pistol," said Xu, who is from the northeastern city of Changchun.
</P>
<P>
"I was not selected by the team for Monday's free pistol event
but today I am very satisfied with my results in the final. It was
also the victory for the whole Chinese team."
</P>
<P>
In the team event, world championship gold medalist China,
formed by the same trio, produced a record-breaking 1,742 points
to improve the previous Asian Games record by one point.
</P>
<P>
Japan won the silver with 1,723, two points ahead of bronze
medalist South Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
