<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices ended higher in
Tokyo Wednesday, led mainly by export-oriented high-tech blue
chips.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 123.70 points, or 0.84
percent, from Tuesday's close to end at 14,931.90.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, gained 8.75 points or 0.77 percent to
1,140.74.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section came to an estimated 360 million
shares, almost unchanged from Tuesday's 356.08 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Growing expectations that the ruling Liberal Democratic Party
and the Liberal Party will form a coalition government and
implement large-size tax cuts boosted retailers, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Market focus is now on next Monday's release of the Tankan
quarterly report on business sentiment by the Bank of Japan, they
said.
</P>
<P>
As investors are expected to remain hesitant to buy and sell
stocks until then, the key index will stay in a tight range for
the rest of the week, they added.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outnumbered
losers 623 to 490, with 177 issues remaining unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
