<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Kill 15 People in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people were killed
Tuesday in two separate traffic incidents in Kenya, the East African
Standard newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Eight people died Tuesday morning when two buses collided
head-on along the Thika-Naivasha Road nearby Nairobi, which also
left 30 other passengers seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Twelve of the critically injured, including an infant, were
admitted at Thika District Hospital.
</P>
<P>
In another accident, 7 people
died along Nyeri-Nyahururu Road in central Kenya when a Nissan
bus they were traveling was overturned a few kilometers from
Nyeri Town.
</P>
<P>
Central Province Traffic Police Enforcement Officer, William
Kabutha, said that 11 others were still in hospital in serious
conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
