<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Become World's Largest Rubber Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia is expected to become
the world's largest natural rubber producer by 2005 with an
estimated production of 2.7 million tons per annum, chairman of
the Indonesian Association of Rubber Industries Daud Husni Bastari
said.
</P>
<P>
"Such an estimate on the Indonesian natural rubber production
is based on the increasing annual production and expansion of
rubber plantation acreage at an average of about 1.5 to 2.0
percent per annum", he told reporters on Tuesday while attending a
seminar on the prospect of natural rubber in the 21st century in
Medan, capital of North Sumatra.
</P>
<P>
He said Indonesia's rubber plantation covers 2.5 million
hectares which enables it to produce some 1.7 million tons of
natural rubber this year, or an increase by 200,000 tons compared
with that of the previous year's 1.5 million tons.
</P>
<P>
When entering the year 2005 Indonesia is expected to be able to
produce some 2.7 million tons of natural rubber shifting the
position of Thailand, which by that time is to produce some 2.5
million tons of natural rubber, he was quoted by Antara News
Agency Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia, which at present is the world's second largest
producer of natural rubber after Thailand by producing some 2.0
million tons per annum, has an opportunity to increase its
production of the commodity by intensifying its production growth,
Bastari said.
</P>
<P>
According to Bastari, the increasing production of the
commodity will be in line with the increasing rubber consumption
in the world at an average of 2.0 percent per annum up to the year
2000 and increase to 2.5 percent per annum up to the year 2020.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
