<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Government Grain Depots Built in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a large depot
for central government grain reserves began recently in the city
of Maoming, Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
This facility, which will have the capacity to store 100 million
kilograms of grain, is one of 14 state grain reserve depots,
with a combined capacity of 1.75 billion kilograms, to be built in
Guangdong this year.
</P>
<P>
To alleviate the severe grain-depot shortage, the central
government has decided to build new grain depots across the
country, with a total capacity of 25 billion kilograms. The new
facilities are scheduled to be completed before the autumn of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong is a major grain consumer, and has long been
suffering from a shortage of grain warehouses. Most of the state
grain-reserve depots to be built in the province will be located
near ports and railways in major grain-consuming cities.
</P>
<P>
The Maoming State Grain Reserve Depot is near the port of
Maoming. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
