<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Produces 1,000-Ton Hydrogenated Reactors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- China No.1 Heavy-Duty
Machine-Building Group in China's northernmost Heilongjiang
Province has now created two 1,000-ton hydrogenated reactors.
</P>
<P>
The reactors were built for the Qilu Petrochemical Company of
Shandong Province and were shipped out on December 6. They are the
largest reactors of their kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The group based in Qiqihar City, Heilongjiang Province, beat
out two foreign competitors in public bidding for the job.
</P>
<P>
The cylindrical reactors are 36 meters long and have an
internal diameter of 3.8 meters and 270-mm-thick walls. They took
13 months to produce.
</P>
<P>
The reactors will be fitted into in Qilu Company's cracking
facility with an annual production capacity of 1.4 million
tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
