<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Loan to Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
said here Wednesday that it has approved an 80 million U.S. dollar
loan to Sri Lanka for road upgrading projects.
</P>
<P>
In a press release, the Manila-based bank said that some 345
kilometers of main roads and 47 bridges in Sri Lanka will be
upgraded with the ADB loan.
</P>
<P>
The road network improvement project will benefit 2.5 million
people living in 11 districts in the central, western and southern
regions of the country, it said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said that it is also providing a technical assistance
grant of 640,000 dollars to promote measures to reform and
strengthen road sector institutions in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
