<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts Int'l Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Second Shanghai
International Automobile Parts and Maintenance Equipment
Exhibition opened in the Shanghai International Exhibition
Center here today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition features automobile engines, parts, chassis,
body parts, and electronic parts and equipment, as well as
maintenance equipment.
</P>
<P>
The four-day exhibition has attracted 300 companies from the
United States, Italy, Australia, Canada, France, Germany and China.
</P>
<P>
Automobile manufacturing has developed into one of China's
pillar industries, with the industry's annual output increasing by
an average of 13 percent over the past two decades. China ranked
11th in the world with 1997 output of 1.58 million units.
</P>
<P>
The industry's total import-export volume jumped from 540
million US dollars in 1978 to 2.68 billion dollars in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
