<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Increases Raw Materials Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Customs reported a 22
percent increase in imports of plastic raw materials such as PVC,
polyester chips, polythene and polypropylene during the first 11
months of the year.
</P>
<P>
The city imported 682,000 tons of related products valued at
629 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Related imports have jumped 45.6 percent since September. The
city's general trade imports grew by 149,000 tons, or 1.2 times
the level for last year's same period and 1.4 times than the
volume for the first eight months of the year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the sharp increase to China's intensified
anti-smuggling campaign in place since July, as well as expanded
infrastructure construction and low prices for materials on the
international market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
