<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tongling Chemical Commences Phosphate Fertilizer Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Tongling Chemical Industry
Group, one of China's major phosphate fertilizer manufacturers, is
installing a new production line at a cost of 422.5 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The new line will increase the group's phosphate fertilizer
production capacity by 160,000 tons annually.
</P>
<P>
An official with the State Administration of Petroleum and
Chemical Industries said the new line will help balance the
ratio between nitrogenous and phosphate fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
The group also plans to upgrade the technology of existing
facilities.
</P>
<P>
The project will be completed within two years and the company
expects annual sales to hit 56 million yuan and net profit to
37.52 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The group currently produces 60,000 tons of phosphoric acid,
120,000 tons of phosphate fertilizer and 200,000 tons of sulfuric
acid annually. The new facility is expected to raise the annual
output of phosphoric acid to 140,000 tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
