<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Increases Housing Construction Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's major
commercial and financial center, has accumulated housing
construction funds totalling 21.4 billion yuan (2.6 billion US
dollars) over the past seven years since the initiation of housing
reform.
</P>
<P>
Some 3.8 million Shanghainese currently contribute to the
municipality's housing construction funds.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Shanghai Housing Capital
Administration Center show that over 20 billion yuan has been
allocated for construction and housing purchases, including
mortgage loans of over 1.8 billion yuan to individuals. The fund
has already provided assistance to over 130,000 Shanghai families.
</P>
<P>
Local sources note that the accumulation system has developed
rapidly over the past two years, with year's loan volume
surpassing total commercial loans by some 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The volume of funds accumulated this year have already doubled
last year's level, and the housing loan has jumped from 12,100
yuan in 1992 to 80,700 yuan per household.
</P>
<P>
Experts anticipate continued growth for the city's real estate
market in 1999, and the level of accumulated funds is expected
to hit 10 billion yuan early next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
