<HEADLINE> Dhaka Hosts BIMST-EC Bazaar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- An 11-day bazaar of products from
 Bangladesh, India, Myanmar, Sri Lanka and Thailand, the five
members of the Bangladesh-India-Myanmar-Sri Lanka-Thailand
Economic Cooperation (BIMST-EC) forum, started here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The bazaar, which preceded a BIMST-EC ministerial-level meeting
scheduled to be held here on December 17-19, was the first
economic and business event within the framework of the BIMST-EC
since its establishment in Bangkok, Thailand in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
The bazaar would become an regular event to be held every year
afterwards by the five countries in turn, A.S.M. Quashem, chairman
of the BIMST-EC forum, said at the inaugural ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Some 50 companies participated in the bazaar, displaying a wide
array of products as well as traditional country food from the
five countries. 
