of renewable energy technologies for sustainable development has
been held here to boost the country's energy production.
</P>
<P>
The workshop, which took place on Tuesday, was jointly
sponsored by the Myanmar Ministry of Science and Technology, and
the Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific
(ESCAP).
</P>
<P>
Attended the workshop were Deputy Minister of Science and
Technology Brigadier-General Thura Aung Ko, delegates of the
United Nations Development Program, officials of concerned
departments and the Yangon Institute of Technology.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the workshop discussed works for energy
production including that of solar energy, windpower and biomass.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar formed the Ministry of Science and Technology in
October 1996, aimed at effectively undertaking scientific and
technological works in the country.
</P>
<P>
