<HEADLINE> EU Sees New Era of Cooperation with SAARC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) is
confident that its relations with South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC) will see a new era of cooperation
under the chairpersonship of Sri Lankan President Kumaratunga, the
official Daily News reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that Sri Lanka is quite strong in its advocacy on
SAARC issues," Carlos Camino Munoz, head of external relations
(SAARC) of the EU, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Munoz told the paper that he believes President
Kumaratrunga will do her best to cooperate and motivate SAARC
nations to achieve the region's economic goals during her
chairpersonship.
</P>
<P>
In the SAARC region, Sri Lanka is known as a highly literate
nation. It is also known as a country producing quality goods
which play a major role in trade specially with the EU, he said.
</P>
<P>
Recently, the EU has shown a keen interest in strengthening
ties with Asian groupings such as SAARC and ASEAN (Association of
Southeast Asian Nations). As the EU expands its activities in the
global scene, its importance to countries like Sri Lanka grows
correspondingly, Munoz said.
</P>
<P>
In this context the EU and SAARC had signed a Memorandum of
Understanding, under which SAARC will benefit in the areas of
exchange of information, external relations and trade and training
for officials of SAARC institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
