<TEXT>
<P>
BATTAYA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Uzbekistan quartet
clocked the best of 3:10.44 to take the men's K-4 1000 meters
canoeing title at the 13th Asian Games here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The champion squad was composed of Rafael Islamov, Andrey
Shilin, Vladimir Kazantsev and Konstantin Yashin.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia moved from third place to second as Kazakhstan was
disqualified for competing in a wrong lane.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesians clocked 3:14.64, beating China to third in
3:16.75. 
</P>
