<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenyang Residents Enjoy Improved Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, capital of northeast
China's Liaoning Province, has made significant headway in
improving air pollution.
</P>
<P>
The density of suspended particles has dropped 9.4 percent and
sulphur dioxide by 18 percent on last year's levels. The annual
volume for dust has dropped to 7,426 tons and that for sulphur to
4,859 tons, according to the local environmental protection bureau.
</P>
<P>
The government of Shenyang, which suffers serious air pollution
in winter due to burning large amounts of coal for heating, has
banned the use of high sulphur coal. It has also allocated over 15
million yuan to update boilers and dust removal facilities.
</P>
<P>
The ban on leaded gasoline has also contributed to the improved
air quality, according to the official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
