<HEADLINE> China's Former FM Spokesman Resumes Office in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Tang Guoqiang, former
spokesman for the Chinese Foreign Ministry, has assumed his office
as deputy commissioner of the ministry's office of commissioner in
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Tang arrived in Hong Kong on Tuesday to succeed Zhao Jihua, who
left his post for Beijing on October 30, a press release issued by
the office said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, Tang, 47, began to work in the
Chinese Foreign Ministry in 1974.
</P>
<P>
He has successively worked in the ministry's Translation
Department, the United Nations Office in Geneva, the Chinese
Embassy in Papua New Guinea, the ministry's Information Department
and the Chinese Embassy in Britain. Tang, married with a son,
served as Spokesman for the Foreign Ministry from September 1996.
</P>
