<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Seizes Massive Haul of Explosives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan army has seized
a massive haul of explosives from a Tamil rebel base in the Jaffna
Peninsula, military sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday troops found about 400 kilograms of high explosives
in a Tamil rebel base at Alaveddy, on information provided by
civilians, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest explosives recovery made since the Jaffna
Peninsula came under the government control in early 1996,
analysts here noted.
</P>
<P>
The haul also included fifty detonators, 25 meters of detonator
cord and five meters of fuse wire. No arrests have so far been
made in this connection, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a 15-year war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
