<HEADLINE> Tyson, Botha to Fight on January 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The fight between Mike
Tyson and Francois Botha has been set on January 16, it was
announced at a news conference today in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
The 12-round bout at the MGM Grand in Las Vegas, will be
Tyson's first since June 28, 1997 when he bit Evander Holyfield's
ears in their heavyweight championship bout and was disqualified
in the third round.
</P>
<P>
The fight will be carried on Showtime Event Television Pay Per
View.
</P>
<P>
When asked how he felt about a possible return to prison,
Tyson said:"I'm not much for talking. You guys know what I do. I
know no one believe that Botha is going to beat me."
</P>
<P>
Asked what round he'd stop Botha, Tyson replied:" Come to the
fight, brother."
</P>
<P>
He aslo said:"I'm not here because I've been voted the nicest
guy in the world. I'm just here to give good fights, be a good
boy."
</P>
<P>
Tyson has a 45-3 recorde with 39 knockout, while Botha, from
South Africa, is 39-1 with 24 knockouts.
</P>
<P>
Botha's only loss came in 1996 by Michael Moorer for the IBF h
eavyweight title. Batha has fought just twice this year.
</P>
<P>
"He's in for a rude awakening, that's all I can say," Botha
said. "I come to fight, I don't come to lay down, and that's what
I intend to do." 
</P>
