<DOCNO> XIE19981209.0356 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama Canal Investments Soar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Investments soared this
year in the Panama canal zone after the United States honored its
treaty to return the canal to Panama on December 31, 1999, the
port authorities said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
They cited China's Taiwanese company Evergreen, Hong Kong-based
Hutchinson plant and U.S. General Motors, which have projected
transporting at least one million containers a year through the
canal.
</P>
<P>
A U.S. company based in Kansas City has said it would rebuild
the trans-isthmian railway to boost maritime and port activities.
</P>
<P>
The Arab-U.S. company Alireza-Mobil has planned to invest 25
million U.S. dollars from 1998 to 2001 in a storage area in the
canal zone conceded in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The 326-hectare area includes 36 underground tanks with a total
storage capacity of 1.1 million barrels of fuel.
</P>
<P>
The port authorities also noted that the Petroport company
received in 1990 a 20-year renewable concession on 10 hectares
where it built 12 storage tanks with a capacity of 120,000 gallons
each. 
</P>
