<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Martin Schmitt edged
double Olympic champion Kazuyoshi Funaki of Japan to clinch his
fourth season victory in the World Cup ski jumping event in
Predazzo, Italy on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Schmitt, with jumps of 128.5 and 125 meters from the 120-meter
hill, totaled 253.7 points to edge Funaki, who jumped 121.5 and
126 meters, by 3.7 points.
</P>
<P>
Funaki's teammates Noriaki Kasai and Kazuya Yoshioka placed
third and fourth respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the overall standings, Schmitt piled up 460 points,
ahead of Finlander Janne Ahonen's 372 and Funaki's 330.
</P>
<P>
Predazzo, the north Italian resort, will host the world nordic
ski events championships in 2003.
</P>
<P>
The next World Cup round is scheduled at Oberhof, Germany,
this weekend. 
