<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Turnover Up in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange
(SSE), one of the two bourses in China, experienced active
trading last month, with the monthly turnover of 112.48
billion yuan, up 10 percent over the previous month.
</P>
<P>
In November, the SSE Composite Index rose in the first half of
the month, closing at the highest 1300.15 points on the 17th day,
and dropped in the second half, closing at 1247.42 points on the
last trading day of the month.
</P>
<P>
Four new shares were listed on the exchange last month, raising
a total of 1,595 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Investors were concentrated primarily on blue chips in November,
with the Hongqiao Airport ranking first in both A-share trading
and total turnover, followed by Shanghai Automotive and
Sichuan Changhong.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, B-share trading continued its downward trend last
month, with the B-share index closing at 30.37 points, 8.6 percent
lower than in the previous month.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the exchange had a total
turnover of 1,190 billion yuan in the first 11 months of this
year, down slightly compared with the same period of last
year. 
