<HEADLINE> Tyson Waiting for Judge's Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The judge who sentenced
Mike Tyson to prison for rape can have three choices regarding
the former heavyweight champion's probation.
</P>
<P>
Putting him to jail is one of them.
</P>
<P>
Judge Patricia Gifford said Monday:" there are three things
could occur when the report is received. A warrant for Mr.
Tyson's arrest could be issue, a hearing on the report could be
scheduled, or there could be no action toward a possible
revocation of probation taken until sentencing in Maryland."
</P>
<P>
Tyson pleaded no contest to misdemeanor assault charges in
Maryland last week, and that could be used as evidence by the
judge to throw him to jail.
</P>
<P>
"Until I've received the report and made a decision, it would
be inappropriate to comment on possible action," Gifford said.
</P>
<P>
Sentencing is expected early next year.
</P>
<P>
Tyson came out from prision in 1995 after Gifford added four
years of probation, meaning Tyson could be sent back to jail for
any further violation. He has violated terms of his probation as
a result of his no-contest plea.
</P>
<P>
Tyson's no-contest plea stemmed from a minor traffic accident
in August in which two motorists claimed Tyson kicked and punched
them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
