<HEADLINE> IDB Supports Private Investment in Uruguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) on Tuesday approved a 155
million-U.S. dollar loan to Uruguay to assist the development of
financial markets in a bid to enhance private investment.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be used to boost medium- and long-term
financing for private investment projects aimed at the
diversification, improvement and expansion of productive
activities, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
