<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Israel, Palestine Talk on Differences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 8 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Middle East Peace Envoy
Dennis Ross Tuesday called on the Palestinians and Israel to
bridge their differences through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Ross, who arrived here earlier in the day, made the call at a
meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
Ross said U.S. President Bill Clinton's visit to the region,
which will start Saturday, will help solve the dispute between
Israel and the Palestinian National Authority (PNA).
</P>
<P>
Ross stressed that as the person who was instrumental in
reaching the Wye peace agreement between Israel and the PNA,
Clinton can also help when there is trouble in implementing the
deal.
</P>
<P>
With the mediation of the U.S., Israel and the PNA signed the
Wye accord on October 23, under which Israel will pull out from
a further 13 percent of the West Bank in exchange for tougher
Palestinian actions against Islamic militants.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Israel is supposed to free 750 Palestinian prisoners
by the end of January, 1999. Last month, 250 of them were
released, but most were criminals, not the political prisoners
demanded by the PNA.
</P>
<P>
Demonstrations staged Monday by Palestinians in the West Bank
to press for more release of prisoners are continuing and have
repeatedly erupted into violent street clashes.
</P>
<P>
Israel suspended the implementation of the peace accord last
week, saying that it will further pull out from the West Bank
until the PNA made concessions over such issues as prisoners and
statehood.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians have threatened to declare an independent state
in May next year no matter whether a peace deal with Israel is
reached or not.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting with Ross, Netanyahu stressed that Israel is
serious in asking the PNA to accept these conditions.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to the region, Clinton will take part in the
meeting of the Palestinian National Council (PNC) Monday on the
repeal of anti-Israeli clauses in the Palestinian national charter.
</P>
<P>
Ross said it will be clear for all to see that during the PNC's
meeting the clauses calling for the destruction of Israel will be
revoked.
</P>
<P>
Ross will also meet the PNA Chairman Yasser Arafat Tuesday
night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
